        <headline>Flash Flood Warning issued April 5 at 1:58PM CDT until April 5 at 3:00PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 158 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicates light to moderate rainfall
continues across the warned area. This will prolong or exacerbate
any ongoing flooding issues as the rain will fall on completely
saturated grounds.

HAZARD...Flash flooding caused by thunderstorms.

SOURCE...Radar and automated gauges.

IMPACT...Flash flooding of small creeks and streams, urban areas,
highways, streets and underpasses as well as other poor
drainage and low-lying areas.

Some locations that will experience flash flooding include...
Mena...                            Waldron...
Mansfield...                       Wickes...
Grannis...                         Hatfield...
Oden...                            Vandervoort...
Beauchamp...                       Opal...
Mena Intermountain Airport...      Polk County Fairgrounds...
Shady...                           Caney Creek Wilderness...
Bard Springs Recreation Area...    Little Missouri Falls Recreation
Area...
Queen Wilhelmina State Park...     Cardiff...
Hartley...                         Cossatot River State Park...
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
